text.tspan: 6.5.1PRIOR DOCKING / REPAIRS1) TA-003 - HSE questionnaire is to be filled by appropriate yard before it can be considered for a quotation. Shipyards beingconsidered for docking/ repairs are to be evaluated first from the declaration received and must meet minimum criteria as per thecontractor’s assessment form. Request for tenders is then made from accredited shipyard in the area where docking is expected.2) The underwriters are to be informed before docking / repairs if any repairs related to H&M cases will be taken up in the yard.3) Owners may be consulted regarding Owner’s requirements, if any, with regards to funnel markings, topside colour and if anyStandard Penalty Clause to be included.4) Specifications to be compared on total time, payment terms, deviation, penalty clause and cost. Yard’s experience with regards tocritical jobs, weather, yard congestion, quotation reliability, port cost, possibility of strikes, deviation etc to be also taken into accountwhen comparing.5) Quotations from yards: a) Total time for repairs – Generally the day of arrival is not counted. To take into account the different considerations of the yards,eg: the term running days denotes all days including weekends and public holidays while working days do not include weekends andpublic holidays. In Europe and Singapore, if the vessel arrives on a Friday, then the 1st day is counted from Monday. b) Total costs – All inclusive will be Shipyard quotation + Non shipyard costs + Paints/Stores/Spares + Superintendent attendance +Agents disbursement + Specialist attending + Class attendance + Deviation cost6) Keep a copy of the message where owners have given their approval of the total Dry dock / repair cost estimate.7) The comparison of the paint quotations to be made taking into account, type of paint, solid content, spread rates, curing time,coating intervals, abrasion resistance, past experience, suitability for trading waters and interval between docking,8) Once yard is confirmed, superintendent shall forward the relevant drawings to the yard, advise the docking draft and trim to thevessel and keeps yard updated with vessel’s ETA. Vessel is asked to arrive at the yard by the most expeditious route to the port ofdry-dock from her last port and requested to revert with distance and steaming time to the port of dry-dock. All care shall be taken toprevent extra steaming so as to minimise the off-hire period. Deviation statement to be requested from master before vessel proceedsto the yard.9) Vessel will be inspected by the chemist to certify her gas free status and acceptability for docking.
